  "page": "Aerion Targaryen (disambiguation)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The name <b>Aerion Targaryen</b> can refer to the following characters:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Aerion_Targaryen_(son_of_Daemion)\" title=\"Aerion Targaryen (son of Daemion)\">Aerion Targaryen</a>, a Lord of Dragonstone, the son of Lord Daemion Targaryen, and the father of King Aegon I Targaryen and his sister-wives, Queens Visenya and Rhaenys Targaryen</li>\n<li>Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aerion_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerion Targaryen\">Aerion Targaryen</a>, also known as <i>Aerion the Monstrous</i> and <i>Aerion Brightflame</i>, the second born son of King Maekar I Targaryen and Lady Dyanna Dayne</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404024206\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.003 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.003 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 4/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 1/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:11165-0!canonical and timestamp 20260404024206 and revision id 194938\n -->\n",
